CREATED:20260208T210843Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260208T210843Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: History of Parkdale
X-SOURCE-URL:https://www.meetup.com/the-history-of-parkdale/
UID:event_312865212@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260322T053207Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260329T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260329T140000
SUMMARY:The Junction! Keele Street and Dundas Street West!
DESCRIPTION:Toronto History Walks\n\\*\\***The Toronto History Walks Yearl
 y Pass is available. Get it now for $125.00 for 1 year of unlimited tours\
 , email**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n**for more information or fo
 r signing up!\\*\\***\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the ticke
 t amount when booking your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to the 
 following email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n\nThe West Toron
 to Junction is back! It has been reworked and a new route explores more of
  this historic area. Prior to this\, the walk crossed Dundas to the north\
 , this tour remains on the southern side and extends to Keele Street and t
 he real industrial heart of the area.\n\nOne of Toronto's most walkable an
 d fascinating neighbourhoods\, and is steeped in history.\n\nLocated in To
 ronto's west end\, west of Lansdowne Avenue\, the area is surrounded on th
 ree sides by railway lines: the CNR mainline to the west\, Metrolinx to th
 e east\, and the CPR east-west line to the north. Dundas Street is the hea
 rt and main street of the Junction\, but also provides the area with a sou
 thern boundary\, creating a compact well defined neighbourhood.\n\nThe vil
 lage was a centre for industry\, and was lined with railway tracks hence t
 he name the Junction. Paint\, ceramics\, chemicals\, and the Ontario Stock
  Yards were also nearby. Industry gave way to the worker's residences\, an
 d by the 1950s the neighbourhood was multicultural consisting of Maltese\,
  Italian\, Polish\, and Macedonian immigrants. Later\, the area became pre
 dominantly Portuguese.\n\nThis area was also an area of churches set in a 
 garden like setting. Now most of the churches have been converted to resid
 ences\, but we still have them as historic markers of a lost era.\n\nThis 
 walk is for all fitness levels.\n\nThe meeting place for our walking adven
 ture is outside the Annette Street Branch of the Toronto Public Library at
  145 Annette Street in West Toronto\, just a block south of Dundas Street 
 West.\n\nThis tour has a ticket price of $15.00 per person!\n\n\\*\\* **Pl
 ease note: Please e-transfer the ticket amount when booking your space for
  this tour! You can e-transfer to the following email at:**\n**torontohist
 orywalks@gmail.com**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/the-history-of-parkdale/events/312865
 212/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260113T172918Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260113T172918Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: History of Parkdale
X-SOURCE-URL:https://www.meetup.com/the-history-of-parkdale/
UID:event_313270219@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260322T053207Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260331T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260331T130000
SUMMARY:Historic Buildings Walking Tour!
DESCRIPTION:Toronto History Walks\n\\*\\***The Toronto History Walks Explo
 rer Pass is available. Get it now for $125.00 for 1 year of unlimited tour
 s\, email**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n**for more information or 
 for signing up!\\*\\***\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the tic
 ket amount when booking your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to th
 e following email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n\nToronto has 
 a rich history\, and it's all around us\, but certain buildings do stand o
 ut and tell our story. On this walking tour the following buildings are ex
 plored and their history revealed. This new tour is for residents and tour
 ists who want to reconnect with their city\, or get to know it from a diff
 erent vantage point!\n\n* Daniel Brooke Building\n* St. Lawrence Hall\n* S
 t. James Anglican Cathedral\n* St. Michael's Cathedral\n* Mackenzie House\
 n* Massey Hall\n* Old City Hall\n* Osgoode Hall\n* Campbell House Museum\n
 * Gooderham Building\n\nand a few other hidden surprises along the way fro
 m the Toronto Stock Exchange to the New City Hall and a few others in betw
 een!\n\nThis walking tour is for all walking levels. Please dress for the 
 season\, and hope to see you there.\n\nPlease meet in front of the iconic 
 St. Lawrence Hall at the corner of Jarvis and King Street East\, we end th
 e tour at Historic Campbell House!\n\nThis tour has a ticket price of $15.
 00 per person.\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the ticket amoun
 t when booking your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to the followi
 ng email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/the-history-of-parkdale/events/313270
 219/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260208T212600Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260208T212600Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: History of Parkdale
X-SOURCE-URL:https://www.meetup.com/the-history-of-parkdale/
UID:event_312786189@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260322T053207Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260404T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260404T150000
SUMMARY:The Disappearance of Ambrose Small! Interactive Game and Tour
DESCRIPTION:Toronto History Walks\n\\*\\***The Toronto History Walks Explo
 rer Pass is available. Get it now for $125.00 for 1 year of unlimited tour
 s\, email**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n**for more information or 
 for signing up!\\*\\***\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the tic
 ket amount when booking your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to th
 e following email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n\nYou will pla
 y detective in this interactive walking tour. Part game\, part walking tou
 r. So get your powers of deduction dusted off\, lace up your runners and l
 et's begin. Only the brightest are allowed on board this tour!\n\nThis tou
 r is included as part of the Toronto History Walks Explorer Pass Package\,
  PRESTO not included! For more information on the Pass please email or get
  in touch here!\n\nThis interactive walking tour discusses the life and ti
 mes of Ambrose Small who disappeared in 1919. Let's try and figure out who
  did what and why! And where is the hapless Mr. Small.\n\nOne of Toronto's
  enduring cold cases\, we explore the world of Mr. Small\, the owner of th
 e Grand Opera House.\n\nWith 25 stops this tour traces the movements of Mr
 . Small prior to his disappearance\, and the theories\, new and old\, behi
 nd that disappearance\, all from the point of view of Mr. Small himself.\n
 \nWe explore Toronto in 1919\, and look back at the life he led and the pe
 ople he came in contact with. It's a whodunit! So shall we begin?\n\n**Thi
 s tour requires a PRESTO card for TTC as this tour uses transit to get aro
 und the city for stops outside the downtown core. One could call it a hop 
 on hop off walking tour!**\n\nOur walk begins at the **Dog Fountain** at B
 erczy Park! We end at the reference Library at Yonge Street and Bloor Stre
 et East.\n\nThis tour has a ticket price of $15.00 per person!\n\n\\*\\* *
 *Please note: Please e-transfer the tour price when booking your space for
  this tour! You can e-transfer to the following email at:**\n**torontohist
 orywalks@gmail.com**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/the-history-of-parkdale/events/312786
 189/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260108T160124Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260108T160124Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: History of Parkdale
X-SOURCE-URL:https://www.meetup.com/the-history-of-parkdale/
UID:event_313004853@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260322T053207Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260405T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260405T130000
SUMMARY:1918 Spanish Flu: Impact on Toronto ( BY DEMAND! ONLY TOUR DATE FO
 R 2026)
DESCRIPTION:Toronto History Walks\n\\*\\***The Toronto History Walks Yearl
 y Pass is available. Get it now for $125.00 for 1 year of unlimited tours\
 , email**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n**for more information or fo
 r signing up!\\*\\***\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the ticke
 t price when booking your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to the f
 ollowing email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n\nIn 1918\, Toron
 to struggled to carry on in a world without hope. A world of violence and 
 death. With the coming end of WW1 in sight\, Toronto and Canada glimpsed h
 ope for the first time in 4 years. But something worse was on the horizon\
 , something unseen\, worse than the trenches and the death from poison gas
 . It was a killer that encircled the globe and struck down victims in mere
  hours\, soldiers and civilians alike\, children and adults\, and was call
 ed the Spanish Flu. In time millions would succumb to the monster.\n\nWith
  the hundreds of troop ships\, and the war still ravaging Europe\, the dis
 ease spread unchecked. Wave after wave of influenza engulfed entire countr
 ies. Entire populations were sickened and thousands died in a matter of ho
 urs. The Spanish Flu disappeared as quickly as it appeared in early 1918. 
 But that was a century ago. And we have learned plenty from it.\n\nLearn a
 bout the history of the Spanish Flu and its impact on Toronto\, how we fou
 ght it both on the ground and politically\, and how it eventually disappea
 red. And to see that our world is different and our health measures are st
 ronger. We are in a better position because of the Spanish Flu.\n\n**This 
 is a living history tour!** This walking tour begins on the steps of Old C
 ity Hall at the northeast corner of Queen Street West\, and Bay Street. Th
 e tour returns to the start location at the Old City Hall.\n\nThis walking
  tour is for all walking levels. Please dress for the season\, and hope to
  see you there.\n\nThis walk has a ticket price of $15.00 per person. If y
 ou plan to attend please secure your spot early!\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: 
 Please e-transfer the ticket price when booking your space for this tour! 
 You can e-transfer to the following email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gma
 il.com**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/the-history-of-parkdale/events/313004
 853/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260122T151257Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260122T151257Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: History of Parkdale
X-SOURCE-URL:https://www.meetup.com/the-history-of-parkdale/
UID:event_312865265@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260322T053207Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T140000
SUMMARY:Historic Hogg's Hollow
DESCRIPTION:Toronto History Walks\n\\*\\***The Toronto History Walks Yearl
 y Pass is available. Get it now for $125.00 for 1 year of unlimited tours\
 , email**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n**for more information or fo
 r signing up!\\*\\***\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the ticke
 t price when booking your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to the f
 ollowing email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n\nJohn and Willia
 m Hogg\, sons to James Hogg\, subdivided the marshy land that became "Hogg
 s Hollow."\n\nIt took a little time to encourage settlers to develop the l
 and due to the inhospitable environment\, but settlers moved in over the f
 ollowing decades. With the historic village of York Mills adjacent\, a sch
 ool\, post office\, pottery\, blacksmith\, livery\, stable\, store\, cemet
 ery and St. John's Anglican Church served Scottish\, Irish and English imm
 igrants.\n\nThe history of modern Hogg's Hollow began in the 1920s with th
 e creation of lots\, and homes reflected the beauty of the English country
 side. The Baron Renfrew School opened in 1925 to replace a structure at 45
  York Mills Road that was destroyed by fire.\n\nHogg's Hollow is certainly
  far from the tourist centre to the south\, and is well worth exploring. W
 ith Yonge Street its main street\, the community has a fascinating history
  that has long gone uncovered. Give Hogg's Hollow a look and you might sta
 y awhile. I promise!\n\nThis walk is for all walking levels. Please dress 
 for the season and bring water. Our Hogg's Hollow adventure walk begins at
  the Yonge Street doors of the York Mills Subway station. We head south an
 d downhill and return to our starting point. Hope to see you there!\n\nThi
 s tour has a ticket price of $15.00 per person!\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: P
 lease e-transfer the ticket price when booking your space for this tour! Y
 ou can e-transfer to the following email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmai
 l.com**
